IS STUDENT DEBT OUR NEXT BUBBLE?
Traditionally considered to be "good" debt, student debt held by college grads has now exited the realm of what most would
consider to be good. With the latest estimates pushing total U.S. student debt above the $1 trillion arrier-surpassing credit card
or automobile debt-many experts suspect that we are about to burst our next "bubble" (as if we need another). Still, not every
